<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Retire1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Retire,</orth> subst. 1) retreat in war: <bibl n="shak. luc 174" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.326" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 326</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 86</bibl> <cit><quote>(make).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 150</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.8.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 8, 15</bibl> (Ff <emph>retreat</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cor 1.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 6, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 3, 40</bibl>.<lb />2) return: <cit><quote>that to his borrowed bed he make r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 573" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 573</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with a blessed and unvexed r. we will bear home that lusty blood again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.253" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 253</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) repair: <cit><quote>all his behaviours did make their r. to the court of his eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 234</bibl></cit>.
